Ever¬†wonder how the contestants on¬†The Voice¬†choose the songs that they sing? They don‚Äôt exactly.

It turns out that it‚Äôs a joint decision. If it were only up to the singers, they‚Äôd all pick the same songs, says executive producer Audrey Morrissey.

What happens is that the contender gives the producers a list of the songs he would like to perform.

‚ÄúWe have several recordings of (the contestants). We‚Äôve seen them in person. We listen to them again. We cross reference with their list. Then we think, ‚ÄòOK, what is the right song for them to get a push?‚Äô That‚Äôs all we‚Äôre thinking about,‚Äù says Morrissey.

‚ÄúWhat song do we feel they can handle? ‚Ä¶ Often times artistes are not clear on what kind of artiste they want to be. Sometimes they‚Äôre just putting songs on their list that they love and they‚Äôre not really thinking about their personal statement.

‚ÄúI can tell you this: regardless of what people may say at the moment, there is no person that goes on that stage that the song that they ultimately perform and end up with isn‚Äôt a song that derived from their list, or was inspired by their list. ‚ÄúOr that they did not raise their hand and say, ‚ÄòI don‚Äôt feel good about this.‚Äô At any point they can, and their song will be changed.‚Äù ‚Äì Tribune News Service
